Description.1: Open Year Round, Saturday Mornings, Rain or Shine. We are the largest, most diverse producer-only farmers' market in the greater Charlotte area. All market products, except fish, are grown, raised or made within 50 miles of Matthews.​ You'll find freshly harvested produce, naturally-raised meats, local honey, plants, artisan foods and hand-crafted items. We are a 501(c)3 non profit. We proudly accept SNAP/EBT and match dollars up to $50!
Description.19: We are a North Carolina producer/grower market committed to providing local food almost every Saturday year-round. We offer fresh seasonal produce year-round as well as free range eggs, pasture-raised meats, local honey, NC seafood, goat cheese, breads and other baked goods, sauces, condiments, coffee, preserves, confections, beer, wine, prepared foods and much more!
Description.20:
Chapel Hill Farmers’ Market was started in April 2008 by Farmers of Orange, a state non-profit organization created for local farmers by local farmers.  All of our farmers and artisans live within 60 miles of Chapel Hill, NC and bring fresh quality produce, value-added farm products, and crafts to market year-round. 
The market is vendor run and operated by our market manager.  Every dollar spent goes directly to our farmers and vendors.  All items are grown, fished, or created by our farmers and artisans.
Description.179: The Boone Winter Farmers' Market offers a wide range of local products such as fresh produce, meats, bouquets, pottery, prepared foods and preserves, honey, homemade body products, herbal remedies, chocolate, coffee, and so much more!
Description.180: ​The King Street Farmers' Market, powered by Blue Ridge Women in Agriculture is returning for the 2022 season! The market has been operating since 2017! The King Street Market is a spacious, outdoor market that operates every Tuesday from May through October. The King Street Market is designed with working families in mind to give them the perfect opportunity to shop local during the week! We have a variety of vendors including produce, meat, eggs, dairy, bread, baked goods, crafts, soap and more!
Description.182: The mission of Davidson Farmers Market is to sponsor a weekly farmers' market in Davidson which provides locally grown food, educates the public about nutrition and the importance of eating locally grown foods and offers musical entertainment, special events and cooking and other demonstrations to create a community festival for the Town. DFM’s goal is to create a vibrant community gathering place with locally grown agricultural and horticultural products and family-friendly educational, musical and entertainment activities.
